site_title        = Official website\n}}\n'''''The Last O.G.''''' is an American [[Television comedy|comedy]] television series created by [[Jordan Peele]] and John Carcieri that premiered on March 31, 2018, on [[TBS (U.S. TV channel)|TBS]]. The series follows a convict released after serving fifteen years who returns to [[Brooklyn]] to find his old neighborhood has changed, and his ex-girlfriend is raising their children with another man. It stars [[Tracy Morgan]], [[Tiffany Haddish]], [[Allen Maldonado]], [[Ryan Gaul]], Taylor Christian Mosby, Dante Hoagland, and [[Cedric the Entertainer]]. In April 2018, it was announced that the series had been renewed for a second season, which premiered on April 2, 2019. In May 2019, the series was renewed for a third season which premiered on April 7, 2020.<ref name=\"Season 3 Renewal\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/the-last-o-g-tracy-morgan-tiffany-haddish-renewed-season-3-tbs-1202615223/|title='The Last O.G.' Starring Tracy Morgan & Tiffany Haddish Renewed For Season 3 By TBS|work=Deadline Hollywood|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=May 15, 2019|accessdate=May 20, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Season 3 Premiere Date\"/>\n\n==Premise==\nTray is an ex-con who is released from prison for good behavior after serving fifteen years. He returns to his old Brooklyn neighborhood to find that it has become [[Gentrification|gentrified]]. His ex-girlfriend, Shannon (also known by nickname Shay-Shay), is now married to another man named Josh and is raising his twin children Amira and Shahzad. Tray decides to become a better man and a father with the help of the owner of a [[Halfway house|halfway house]], Mullins, and his cousin Bobby.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n===Main===\n* [[Tracy Morgan]] as Tray Barker\n* [[Tiffany Haddish]] as Shannon \"Shay-Shay\" Birkeland\n* [[Allen Maldonado]] as Bobby Barker\n** Maldonado also plays Clyde Barker, Bobby's deceased older brother\n* [[Ryan Gaul]] as Josh Birkeland\n* Taylor Christian Mosby as Amira Birkeland\n* Dante Hoagland as Shahzad Birkeland\n* [[Cedric the Entertainer]] as Miniard Mullins (Main Season 1, Recurring Season 2)\n\n===Recurring===\n* Joel Marsh Garland as Big Country\n* Gino Vento as Gustavo\n* Derek Gaines as Jason \"Jaybird\" Watkins\n* Daniel J. Watts as Felony\n* Dimitri Joseph Moise as Mostel Defferies\n* [[Malik Yoba]] as Wavy\n* [[Edi Patterson]] as Elizabeth\n* Miles G. Jackson as Benjamin\n* Natalie Carter as Ruth\n* Byrne Davis, Jr. as Billy C.\n* [[Randy Gambill]] as Jason\n* [[Bresha Webb]] as Faith\n* [[Method Man]] as Green-Eyes\n\n===Guest===\n* Jon J. Masters as Mr. Washington\n* [[Judith Roberts (actress)|Judith Roberts]] as Mrs. Washington\n* [[Chrissy Metz]] as Pooh Cat\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Series overview\n| color1     = #E3C0BE\n| link1      = #Season 1 (2018)\n| episodes1  = 10\n| start1     = {{Start date|2018|3|31}}\n| end1       = {{End date|2018|6|5}}\n\n| color2     = #2E516C\n| link2      = #Season 2 (2019)\n| episodes2  = 10\n| start2     = {{Start date|2019|3|30}}\n| end2       = {{End date|2019|6|4}}\n\n| color3     = #02D2BA\n| link3      = #Season 3 (2020)\n| episodes3  = \n| start3     = {{Start date|2020|4|7}}\n| end3       =\n}}\n\n===Season 1 (2018)===\n{{Episode table |background=#E3C0BE |overall= |season= |title=25 |director= |writer= |airdate= |viewers=10 |country=U.S. |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n |Title           = Pilot\n |DirectedBy      = [[Jorma Taccone]]\n |WrittenBy       =  John Carcieri & [[Jordan Peele]]\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|3|31}}{{efn|name=fn1|The episode originally aired as a \"sneak peek\" on March 31, 2018. It was later re-aired for its official television premiere on April 3, 2018.}}\n |Viewers         = 1.87<ref>{{cite news|last1=Porter|first1=Rick|title=Saturday cable ratings: Final Four scores for TBS, up from 2016|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/saturday-cable-ratings-march-31-2018/|accessdate=Ap